      <section eId="sec_138_460">
        <num>138.460</num>
        <content>
          <p>for the first time in this state which was registered in another state that levied a tax substantially identical to the tax levied under this section, the person shall be entitled to receive a credit against the tax imposed by this section equal to the amount of tax paid to the other state. A credit shall not be given under this subsection for taxes paid in another state if that state does not grant similar credit for substantially identical taxes paid in this state.</p>
          <p>a nonrefundable credit shall be given against the tax imposed by subsection (1) of this section for the sales and use tax paid.</p>
        </content>
